          "_sourceTheme": "startm5",
          "_customHTML": "<section data-bs-version=\"5.1\" class=\"article07\" group=\"Article\" data-bg-video=\"{{bg.type == 'video' && bg.value.url}}\" mbr-class=\"{\n    'mbr-fullscreen': fullScreen,\n    'mbr-parallax-background': bg.parallax}\">\n    <mbr-parameters>\n        <header>Size</header>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Full Screen\" name=\"fullScreen\">\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Full Width\" name=\"fullWidth\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Top\" name=\"paddingTop\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" step=\"1\" value=\"5\" condition=\"fullScreen == false\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Bottom\" name=\"paddingBottom\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" step=\"1\" value=\"5\" condition=\"fullScreen == false\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Width\" name=\"contentWidth\" min=\"6\" max=\"12\" value=\"8\" step=\"1\">\n        <header>Show/Hide</header>\n        <input type=\"range\" title=\"Paragraphs Amount\" name=\"articlesAmount\" min=\"1\" max=\"10\" value=\"3\" step=\"1\">\n        <header>Background</header>\n        <fieldset type=\"background\" name=\"bg\">\n            <input type=\"image\" title=\"Image\" value=\"/addons/socialm5/components/_images/background1.jpg\">\n            <input type=\"color\" title=\"Color\" value=\"#fff8ef\" selected>\n        </fieldset>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Overlay\" name=\"overlay\" condition=\"bg.type !== 'color'\" checked>\n        <input type=\"color\" title=\"Overlay Color\" name=\"overlayColor\" value=\"#ffffff\" condition=\"overlay && bg.type !== 'color'\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Opacity\" name=\"overlayOpacity\" min=\"0\" max=\"1\" step=\"0.1\" value=\"0.3\" condition=\"overlay && bg.type !== 'color'\">\n    </mbr-parameters>\n\n    <div class=\"mbr-overlay\" mbr-if=\"overlay && bg.type !== 'color'\" opacity=\"{{overlayOpacity}}\" bg-color=\"{{overlayColor}}\"></div>\n\n    <div mbr-class=\"{\n            'mbr-fullscreen': fullScreen}\">\n        <div mbr-class=\"{'container': !fullWidth, 'container-fluid': fullWidth}\">\n            <div class=\"row\">\n                <div class=\"col-12 col-md-{{contentWidth}}\">\n                    <div class=\"row\">\n                        <div class=\"col-12\">\n                            <p class=\"mbr-text mbr-fonts-style\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-4\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-text\">\n                            </p><h1>Understanding Houston Guardianship</h1><p>When age, illness, or injury leaves a loved one without the capacity to manage their own personal or financial affairs, guardianship is an option that can be considered. However, it is not a one-size-fits-all solution, and there are several recognized alternatives that may be more appropriate to the individual’s circumstances. Our <a href=\"https://www.wthompsonlaw.com/guardianship/\" class=\"text-primary\" target=\"_blank\">guardianship attorneys near me</a> can provide guidance to help you understand your options and choose the right arrangement.\n<br>\n<br>A legal guardian is a person appointed by the court to oversee an incapacitated ward’s personal well-being and/or finances. The term “ward” refers to an adult who, due to injury, disease, disability, or the natural aging process, has lost the ability to care for his or her own physical and emotional needs. The person may also be a minor who stands to inherit money or property or an individual who cannot sign a power of attorney document due to mental incapacity.\n<br>\n<br>To be considered for appointment as a guardian in Houston guardianship cases, you must undergo a thorough background check and pass a court-appointed test proving your fitness and capacity to serve as a guardian of an adult or a minor. In addition, you must submit a bond and swear an oath to the court that you will faithfully perform your duties and act in the best interests of the ward. Once you are approved, the clerk will issue you “Letters of Guardianship,” which is proof that you are authorized to make decisions for the ward. You must file annual reports and a complete accounting of your actions.\n<br>\n<br>The Houston guardianship process is much longer than a power of attorney proceeding because you must attend a hearing and demonstrate that you are suitable to take on this responsibility. In addition, you must continue to meet the eligibility criteria established by Texas law. If you are appointed as a guardian of an estate, you must submit a detailed account of how you managed the ward’s finances each year to the court.\n<br>\n<br>In many cases, a Houston guardianship can be avoided by the creation of a power of attorney while you are still of sound mind. Our Houston guardianship attorneys can draft a document for you to select the person who will be your agent and specify the powers that they will have. Your power of attorney will not become effective until you have suffered an injury or illness that renders you incapable of handling your own affairs. In most cases, a Houston guardianship will only be necessary when other means of assistance, such as a trust or joint accounts, have been unsuccessful in meeting the ward’s needs. Our firm can also assist you in establishing less restrictive alternatives to Houston guardianship. For example, a supported decision-making agreement is an alternative to a full guardianship in which the ward enters into an agreement with a supporter who helps them make decisions and supports their independence. A statutory representative payee can be another alternative to guardianship, but only for the management of public benefits.&nbsp;<br></p>\n                         \n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</section>",
