          "_customHTML": "<section data-bs-version=\"5.1\" class=\"article07\" group=\"Article\" data-bg-video=\"{{bg.type == 'video' && bg.value.url}}\" mbr-class=\"{\n    'mbr-fullscreen': fullScreen,\n    'mbr-parallax-background': bg.parallax}\">\n    <mbr-parameters>\n        <header>Size</header>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Full Screen\" name=\"fullScreen\">\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Full Width\" name=\"fullWidth\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Top\" name=\"paddingTop\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" step=\"1\" value=\"5\" condition=\"fullScreen == false\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Bottom\" name=\"paddingBottom\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" step=\"1\" value=\"5\" condition=\"fullScreen == false\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Width\" name=\"contentWidth\" min=\"6\" max=\"12\" value=\"8\" step=\"1\">\n        <header>Show/Hide</header>\n        <input type=\"range\" title=\"Paragraphs Amount\" name=\"articlesAmount\" min=\"1\" max=\"10\" value=\"3\" step=\"1\">\n        <header>Background</header>\n        <fieldset type=\"background\" name=\"bg\">\n            <input type=\"image\" title=\"Image\" value=\"/addons/socialm5/components/_images/background1.jpg\">\n            <input type=\"color\" title=\"Color\" value=\"#fff8ef\" selected>\n        </fieldset>\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" title=\"Overlay\" name=\"overlay\" condition=\"bg.type !== 'color'\" checked>\n        <input type=\"color\" title=\"Overlay Color\" name=\"overlayColor\" value=\"#ffffff\" condition=\"overlay && bg.type !== 'color'\">\n        <input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Opacity\" name=\"overlayOpacity\" min=\"0\" max=\"1\" step=\"0.1\" value=\"0.3\" condition=\"overlay && bg.type !== 'color'\">\n    </mbr-parameters>\n\n    <div class=\"mbr-overlay\" mbr-if=\"overlay && bg.type !== 'color'\" opacity=\"{{overlayOpacity}}\" bg-color=\"{{overlayColor}}\"></div>\n\n    <div mbr-class=\"{\n            'mbr-fullscreen': fullScreen}\">\n        <div mbr-class=\"{'container': !fullWidth, 'container-fluid': fullWidth}\">\n            <div class=\"row\">\n                <div class=\"col-12 col-md-{{contentWidth}}\">\n                    <div class=\"row\">\n                        <div class=\"col-12\">\n                            <p class=\"mbr-text mbr-fonts-style\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-4\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-text\">\n                            </p><h2><p>Steps to Establishing Guardianship in Houston</p></h2><p>When a loved one becomes incapacitated through illness, injury, or age, you may worry about their health and well-being. You might also be concerned that they will be unable to manage the essential details of their life, including their living arrangements, medical decisions, and finances. Fortunately, Texas law provides a legal framework designed to assist individuals in these circumstances. This is called Houston guardianship, and it enables an individual to make critical choices for an incompetent adult. It seeks to balance the imperative of protection with the preservation of an individual’s rights and autonomy. In addition to Houston guardianship, there are less restrictive options available that can provide assistance in these situations, such as supported decision-making arrangements or powers of attorney. Consulting with guardianship attorneys near me can help you navigate these options.\n<br>\n<br>The process of obtaining a Houston guardianship begins with filing a petition in court. A judge then schedules a hearing, which you and the proposed ward (unless they are medically frail or otherwise unable to attend) will be required to attend. At this hearing, the judge will evaluate your qualifications and determine whether Houston guardianship is necessary and in the best interests of the ward.\n<br>\n<br>Before the hearing, you will be required to submit a background check. The court will send you instructions on how to complete this. A court investigator is also appointed to interview the proposed ward, family members, social workers, and others to assess the case and make an independent recommendation.\n<br>\n<br>After the hearing, the judge will appoint a guardian to manage the ward’s affairs. The judge will also appoint an attorney ad litem to represent the interests of the proposed ward during the proceeding and advocate for alternative services that might be appropriate.\n<br>\n<br>A guardian must file an oath and bond before they can act on behalf of the ward. The oath affirms that they will perform the duties of a guardian in a responsible and ethical manner. The bond demonstrates that the guardian will not mishandle the ward’s property or finances. Once the oath and bond have been filed, the court will issue letters of guardianship, which must be renewed on an annual basis.\n<br>\n<br>Houston guardianship and conservatorship involve complex processes that require the assistance of an experienced attorney. If you have questions about how to best protect the interests of your loved one, contact a knowledgeable Houston elder law attorney who can provide compassionate guidance.\n<br>\n<br>If you have concerns about your child’s ability to care for themselves, it is important to discuss these issues with an experienced attorney early on. In addition to evaluating your child’s situation, an attorney can help you plan for the future by creating trusts and joint accounts to limit the extent of the protection needed. If you have already begun this process, a lawyer can review your estate planning documents to ensure that they meet state standards. To obtain the support you need, contact an experienced attorney today. To speak with a Houston guardianship and probate attorney, reach out for legal advice.&nbsp;<br></p>\n                         \n                        </div>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</section>",
